Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: sylli
Version: 0.9.8
Summary: SSP Syllabifier - Divides words into syllables
Home-page: http://sylli.sourceforge.net
Author: Iacoponi Luca
Author-email: jacoponi@gmail.com
License: Apache2 License
Description:  Sylli is a universal syllabifier. Developed for Italian, it
        can easily be adapted to any language that is claimed to respect the SSP.
        Sylli divides timit, strings, files and directories into syllables and provides
        other useful functions for syllable analysis
Keywords: NLP,CL,natural language processing,computational linguistics,syllable,syllabification,italian,linguistics,phonology,syllabifier
